caption: A year of keeping that gratitude higher than our expectations 💫🦋🪩🎀 … or just… trying not to have any expectations at all 🤷‍♀️
A year of drawings and sketchbookings in one minute 💫

Lots of time spent looking at bugs, beyond fortunate in family and farm, a good bit in the middle where there was plenty of time for horses, and really my favourite thing is that possum hanging on the screen door at 2am.

Alright, total last minute with these but my annual printable Valentines are up exclusively on my Patreon (plus all the past years’ iterations) 💘🎀💫 

These are printable at home or your local print shop, if like me you are an insufferable last-minuter. 

🌞 My Patreon has been pretty quiet over the past year, with little Goldie taking up most of my time, but the wheels are starting to turn over there again… and thank you to everyone who has/does support me there, it allows me to make the work that I share here and it means the world to me. 

Anyway happy Valentines if you’re into that kinda thing!

Road trips west, wildflowers and scribbly sketchbook sessions 🌻🌼🌞

If you like seeing sketchbook and drawing techniques or processes, or just like a peaceful musing on creativity and some nice wildflowers, I made a cute lil video over on my YooToob 💫

As my Instagram account withers away, I would so greatly appreciate you checking out my videos over there, if you’re into all things sketchbook scribbling, road trip wandering and creative chattering. 

#sketchbook #travelvlog #roadtrip #visittamworth #tamworthnsw #tcmf2024 #visitnsw

Did you know I make short Draw & Explore videos over on my ¥o>+ub3 channel? 

This one was a visit to a slightly @accidentallywesanderson trout hatchery, and then a little walk through the process of drawing said trout in my sketchbook. 

And I also talk a little bit about Rick Rubin’s The Creative Act book and why we’ve gotta act on our creative whims. Maybe I’ll take my own (and Rick’s) advice one day…

Anyway hope you love it and we can go on some more adventures together 💘🐟💫 you know where the /!nk might be!

Drawings in the wildflower blooms on the way west… 

A few of my favourite subjects popping up in this mini-drawing series — the sun, the moon, a bucking horse and some good luck — made with sign pen and @winsorandnewton alcohol markers. 

There are wildflowers everywhere on the drive up the mountain… I can’t remember visiting at this time of year because it’s way too hot, but we’re heading out regardless 🌼
